    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ScrollingBuffer data corruption in imscope plotting\n\n### Summary\nThe imscope plotting functionality in the gNB/UE visualization tools experienced data corruption and incorrect plotting when the ScrollingBuffer reached its maximum capacity. This affected real-time KPI monitoring displays, causing misleading throughput and BLER graphs during extended test sessions.\n\nThe issue occurred because the ScrollingBuffer implementation used circular buffering but the plotting code assumed data was always in chronological order starting from index 0. When the buffer wrapped around, older data appeared as newer data in the plots.\n\nThis manifested as sudden drops to zero in the RB allocation graphs and incorrect BLER calculations that could mislead developers during performance analysis. In some cases, the corrupted data caused assertion failures in the ImPlot library.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/imscope/imscope.cpp`: Added GetPlotData method to ScrollingBuffer to return data in chronological order regardless of buffer state. Updated ShowUeScope to use the new method for plotting KPI data.\n"
}